Package gw.api.databuilder

Class FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

java.lang.Object
gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<FinancialThresholdTrigger,FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder>
gw.api.databuilder.CCDataBuilder<FinancialThresholdTrigger,FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder>
gw.api.databuilder.FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder
All Implemented Interfaces:
DelegateDataBuilder<FinancialThresholdTrigger>, ValueGenerator<FinancialThresholdTrigger>
public class FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder extends CCDataBuilder<FinancialThresholdTrigger,FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder>
A data builder for a FinancialThresholdTrigger, which is used to invoke special handling for a claim when one of its Claim Indicators changes.
Author:
pyoung

  • Constructor Details

    • FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder(CurrencyAmount thresholdAmount)
      The default constructor a FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder. This builder has no value set for the FinancialThreshold on which to trigger. The currency is set to the reporting currency and ThresholdAmount is set to 100.
      Parameters:
      thresholdAmount - the monetary amount used as a threshold

  • Method Details

    • withFinancialThreshold

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder withFinancialThreshold(FinancialThreshold financialThreshold)
      Sets the type of FinancialThreshold that this trigger will test when deciding whether to fire.
      Parameters:
      financialThreshold - a member of the FinancialThreshold typelist indicating the subtype of FinancialThreshold to test.
      Returns:
      the modified FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

    • withTriggeringCause

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder withTriggeringCause(FinancialTriggerCause cause)
      Sets the type of occurrence that this trigger will test when deciding whether to fire.
      Parameters:
      cause - type of financial metric for this trigger to test against
      Returns:
      the modified FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

    • withThresholdAmount

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder withThresholdAmount(CurrencyAmount amount)
      Sets the monetary amount that defines the threshold that this trigger will test when deciding whether to fire. Also sets the currency field based on the amount, if there is one.
      Parameters:
      amount - the monetary amount used as a threshold
      Returns:
      the modified FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

    • withCurrency

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder withCurrency(Currency currency)
      Sets the currency that a claim must have to match this trigger, and which is the currency of ThresholdAmount.
      Parameters:
      currency - the currency that a claim must match and the currency of ThresholdAmount
      Returns:
      the modified FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder

    • withReportingCurrency

      public FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder withReportingCurrency()

      Returns:
      the modified FinancialThresholdTriggerBuilder
